<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="cag_promoter_pcag">CAG Promoter (pCAG)</a> - The CAG promoter is a strong <a href="#promoter">promoter</a> for expressing proteins in mammalian cells. It is composed of <a href="#cmv">Cytolomegalovirus' (CMV)</a> <a href="#promoter">promoter</a> enhancer region, chicken β-Actin promoter its first <a href="#intron">intron</a> and <a href="#exon">exon</a>, finally the rabbit β-Globin splice acceptor. Hence: <strong>C</strong>ytomegalovirus <strong>A</strong>ctin <strong>G</strong>lobin = CAG.